The paper deals with graph simplification, which is a topic in computer science related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and computational geometry, which are covered by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of gate graphs for simplification involves the concept of locality, which is related to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper proposes an efficient mining algorithm, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
